dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded by ITOS as a feature class from UNOCHA. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected when possible and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS: 1. ITOS has added parent attribution matching the features' p-code portions. 2. Found and fixed 6 overlap errors and an estimated 300 gap errors. Due to the large number of features in Admin4, some errors may not be found and corrected in this version.
Users should be aware that: - Admin4 is a places layer that does not cover the national extent. - 38 Admin4 units are outside of their attributed Admin3. - 31 Admin4 units have Admin3 pcodes that do not exist in the Admin3 layer. All are physically located in Admin3 Sevastopol. -173 Admin4 names do not have a 1 to 1 relationship between languages. -121 Admin4 names are not unique within their Admin3.
